The paper deals with the cooperative localization of a team of mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a partially decentralized implementation suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). The reliance on communication links and the need for robustness suggests a possible connection to networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the use of an Extended Kalman filter and the mention of suboptimal solutions suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
